text: I often thought how they got the people to believe, and how they got others to look away . I think that's what was tackled here , Oscar's Isac's character Peter Malkin almost believed. I think we all want to, most all.  Ben's Kingley's character Adolf Eichman thoughts on how he viewed people more as animals was explained in the beginning. It needed to be. Adolf also pleaded with Peter to be heard.  It also was explained to us , the audience , how the SS got Rabbi's to help load the trains with Jews without conflict.  This was said after Peter stated that violence won't break a man, Adolf Eichman,  that could coerce the masses. I once worked with a women who was alive in those times. I politely asked her how did it all evolve. Didn't people notice . She said that they heard humors after awhile. She said how could all of any of it be true, for they were living on the street and hungry, then they weren't. She thought that how could people who did such a good thing, do such horrible things. I was skeptical at this explanation , but when the wall came down she was ecstatic, and that's when I learned that  this women had climbed over the wall and hadn't seen her sister in 40 years. We had coffee and chocolate that day to celebrate. I held her in my arms that day as she cried and shook, for all the reasons that time just can't forget . I collect propaganda pieces . I should say  that moment  is when I started my collection. At the same time in my life , I meet a good Polish fellow and his wife. I asked him many questions regarding life and how it was in Poland. I also asked him for insight in the time frames mentioned above and in Operation Finale , for I thought it was more appropriate . He asked me a simple question first  " How do you think they can get a person to pick up a gun and aim it at another person , and kill them " ? I also collect US WW l&ll posters .  It was important that Adolf showed Peter his wolf inside . It was also important that Joe Awyn's character , Klaus Eichman , Adolf's son , got the necessary information from  stretched girl, in the manner he did.  Why, it should who Adolf was . *_The sins of the father_*   BTW Haley Lu Richardson did a really good job here. She reminded me of a younger Jennifer Connelly Lior Roz pulled his weight here too.  I do look at my collection of propaganda pieces from time to time. I lock them away again in _shame and hope_
